China Executes Three Terrorists - Latest News Briefs - Arutz Sheva
China has executed three separatists today (Tuesday) who were convicted for their participation in a terror attack at a train station in the western region of Xinjiang, that killed more than 30 people last year, Reuters reported.
The terrorists, Iskandar Ehet, Turgun Tohtunyaz and Hasayn Muhammad, were sentenced to death this past September, following their convictions on charges of leading a terror organization and homicide.Â Police killed four additional terrorists during the March 1, 2014 attack, which injured 141 people.